latestIgtvVideos.title: i don’t know my name by grace vanderwaal
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
hi happy 100k whAT 
this whole thing literally started as a joke where i decided to post random snapchat videos i used to send to my friends in a challenge thing. everyone who has voluntarily chosen to see me say the same things on the internet in (only slightly) better lighting, thank you for existing. 

sending pyaar ishq mohabbat to the OG Pankha Gang who’ve followed me since I was at 7k followers and we used to do cute late live sessions and just chat and i think that’s why I feel so comfortable on my page because I got SO lucky with my audience. y’all have never made me feel like I can’t be myself because you love me for exactly that (why you enjoy watching someone who’s a wacko like myself is your own concern) but truly, it’s quite a nice feeling to be loved while simply being you. 

thank you @santu.misra for discovering me and adopting this mei into this new world❤️ 

can’t wait to achieve more milestones with all of u, get those kind DMs that I read all of, and can’t wait to be loved just the same. we will all find our way as we grow bigger, but betadarlinghoneysugarpies, mashallah kya kill kardiye hai kasam se

latestIgtvVideos.title: Desi Parents Reacting To Mental Health Problems
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
what are some things that you've heard that sound like good mental health advice but rlly aren't? 🥴 
✨✨✨✨

PS - how you can possibly approach this topic and unlearn that conditioned stigma if you have said something like this: 
1. don't ever trivialise the issue that someone's bringing up
2. remember!! to!! be kind!! in the way you approach them 
3. don't be scared of professional help
5. remember that it's not a new or generational problem, it's always been around - there's just more awareness now 
6.  access the opportunities and the awareness that exist now, be glad that we're progressing!! 

also link in my bio has free/affordable therapy resources that you can access ❤️
